# Prime My Brain — Cursor AI Rules

## Mandatory Reading
Read these files before making any code changes:
1. `docs/skills/01-monorepo-structure.md`
2. `docs/skills/02-frontend-enforcement.md`
3. `docs/skills/03-backend-enforcement.md`

## Architecture
- Frontend: Elm Architecture (Model/Actions/Update/View/Effects)
- State: Zustand with redux middleware + dispatch pattern
- UI: Mantine v7 (theme-only customization, no CSS modules/Tailwind)
- Forms: @mantine/form + zodResolver
- Backend: PocketBase Go library mode
- Build: Vite only (no webpack/CRA/Next.js)
- Package manager: Bun only

## Code Style
- Actions: discriminated union with `domain/VERB` naming (e.g., `sensor/FETCH_START`)
- Reducers: pure functions only, no side effects
- Effects: all async/side-effect code in `effects/` directory
- Views: receive `(state, dispatch)` props, pure rendering
- Types: derived from Zod schemas via `z.infer<>`

## Forbidden
- Never use Zustand `set()` directly — always use `dispatch()`
- Never put async logic in reducers
- Never add CSS modules, styled-components, or Tailwind
- Never call PocketBase outside `effects/`
- Never use npm/yarn/pnpm
- Never use useState/useReducer for app-level state
